<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-05-12T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-05-12T09:00:00-05:00" n="753" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d753">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">361.11/3724: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schmedeman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Christiania</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-05-12T15:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">May 12,
                                        1921—3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received May 12—2:39
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>19. Your 19, May 10, noon. Nansen much pleased with your message and sees
                            no objection to publication. He thinks of sending the text to the
                            Soviets.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Schmedeman</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>